('52', '15/02/2010 00:00', '', '', 'P', 'Returned call- gave update and asked for prayer. Is attending couple counselling at Cedar House- has one mpore session. However, it is \nnow clear the breakdown in his marriage is irreparable. He is \nconcerned about his two young sons, Henry and James. He has \nasked his solicitor if it would be possible for him to have custody. Will \ncontinue with counselling at CH Told he could phone again if he needed prayer or help.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('52', '14/05/2010 00:00', '', '', 'O', 'John and his wife now separated, but share custody of the children, and live close together. Recently made redundant from his Carnforth \njob, but found two more jobs, one in Lancaster which allows him to \nwork around school hours, and the other which is offering training.\n\nIs recieving counselling at the CH, and speaks highly of their couple counsellor. His relations with his wife are better since separating. No longer has contact with his parent in laws. Is attending King;s Community Church and thinking of training to be a Street Pastor.Informed of Men''s Conference', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('53', '10/08/2009 00:00', 'Barbara', '', 'E', 'Came for hospitality and to talk about his eye problems. Became an Orhtodox Christian when he amrried- this marriage has recently \nbroken down, resulting in his homelessness. He has epilepsy, and \nseveral episodes resulted in his collapse and emergency admissions \nhave increased from 1 per year to 4 or 5 in the month since \nbecoming homeless. Asked for prayer for his accomodation', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
