('59', '24/07/2009 00:00', 'Barbara', '', 'B', 'Offered to go with her to the police station next Tuesday, she would call on Mon to confirm, but wouldn''t leave her tel number. Said we would pray for her, which comforted her,Came because CAB was closed, and she needed legal advice. Has tried several solicitors in Lancaster, and they will not represent her. O see if a previous statement she has made has been investigated. She is a single Mum with a 13 yr old son. He was with her mother, who seems to undermine her authority with him. Her ex lives close by and has ''taken her mother''s side''- she would not say why.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('59', '27/07/2009 00:00', '', '', 'B', 'Came with her son Adam/ She has decided not to go to the police, but seek legal advice. Given list of solicitors, and called on her behalf. Given number of community legal service (0845 345 4345)- passed over phone to Sophia to continue convesation. Gave a number of NSPCC she\n could use. She asked if we could phone them. \nArranged appointment time 1.30, Fri, 31st', 'O', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
