('111', '18/08/2010 00:00', 'Kath', 'Brian rang requesting a visit', 'B', 'Bryan and Kathleen''s relationship is under stress and he is talking about separtation because son is still living with them and his children stay 4 days a week, he is abusing their hospitality and they are short of money although are still working with CCCS. They want to stay together but the pressure is getting to them both but in different ways, she has almost given over to hysteria and he confessed he is afraid to face son up and ask him to go.  I clearly went through their choices, they asked if they could come back to talk again.  They will ring after weekend.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('111', '02/02/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'Bryan rang to update us.  Son is still living with them and his children several days a week.  The kids sneak up to sleep with Dad but Bryan is worried cos they are too old for this but he''s convinced nothing inappropriate is happening.  Has had a suspected stroke and has been in hospital - now out, undergoing tests.', 'i', 'Said we would pray for him and situation but not sure if he believes.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('111', '28/01/2010 00:00', 'Kath', 'Couple having difficulty due to son''s debt and separation with wife.  Son has been lving with them and his children 3 days a week.  They are finding it very stressful and are paying some of his debts and are being harassed by his creditors.  Has been to CAB with his debt.', 'D', 'Recommend they ring CAP - rang back and said they were out of their postcode area.  Recommended CCCS instead.', 'O', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('111', '14/04/2010 00:00', 'Kath', 'Bryan called for some benefits advice for son who is getting divorced and havng his house reposessed.  He''s claiming Incapacity Benefits but has his children 4 days a week.  Trying to claim Tax credits.', 'D', 'Recommended that he check the situation with Child Benefits etc', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
