('164', '06/10/2010 00:00', 'Kath', 'Came in with partner and child as a referral from social worker (CAPS). Emma is in the process of being awarded her partners 3 children by court, but struggling with the practicalities of bedding, clothes, shoes and toys for them.', 'F', 'Gave them emergency food for over the weekend and mentioned asking in our local churches we attend regularly for donations of money or unwanted items to pass on. (Mob phone # above is Emma''s; Martin''s mob # - 07889930963)', '', 'L', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('164', '15/10/2010 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Emma came with Martin to collect the items donated by a school and churches (children''s clothes, toys, books, beddings).', 'O', 'Simon, the older son came with them. Emma said she would like to marry and have a child, but she has cystic ovaries.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('164', '03/02/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Emma called in with Martin to tell us their good news - their application for custody of Simon has been successful.  Emma thanked Kath for her email response.', 'P', 'Emma received prayer for healing of her infected hand.  We were able to give them some donated clothing for Simon.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('164', '11/02/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'Received an email from Emma Hazel regarding food packages for the family (dated 10th February 2011) Called in for food for Martin, Emma and Simon who is now with them full time.  Ema is really depressed, the young boy refused a booklet saying he was a pagan like his mum and dad!', 'F', 'Given food packages  x 3 plus additional food items.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('164', '09/03/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Emma called in with Martin and Simon to collect clothes/bedding.  Martin said the final decision about the custody of his children is Fri (11th) - he is not eating due to worry.  He said their mother had attacked him when he picked up the kids from school', 'O', 'Gave clothes/bedding.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('164', '13/05/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'See Attached email. The family is really struggling and we have therefore given them a further supply of food. We offered to pray.', 'F', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('164', '16/12/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'Emma is pregnant and they are struggling with finances. Their benefit has been stopped, someone reported her as working, but she was in hospital. It is being assessed. Gave them a hamper.', 'F', 'Food', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('164', '26/01/2012 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Emma phoned giving update.  Courts granted them custody of the children.  Their mother has access one weekend in four.  It will take 2/3 months to process benefits claim for Emma and the children.  They have contacted benefit agency.  Family unable to help, have helped in the past.  Have part paid rent with last of money.  Friend unable to pick up food for them.', 'i', 'To phone back tomorrow if we are able to deliver for them.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('164', '20/09/2013 00:00', 'Chris', '', 'F', 'Benefits suspended because one child gone back to birth mother. Phils father has moved due to illness and bedroom. Food given for 2 adults and 3 children.', '', '', '2', '3', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('165', '14/10/2010 00:00', 'Barbara', 'David (a jopiner) was directed by his sister. Living temporarily with daughter. Lancaster-born and bred and has family and friends here. Had private rented accommodation in Morecambe and his landlady terminated the tenancy. Went to Strategic Housing who said he was deliberately homeless as he hadn''t taken his 2 months entitlement. David said her would be intimidated if he did not leave. He has no tenancy arrears.', 'H', 'Has been to YMCA and filled in an application form (rent deposit scheme). Has alcohol issues; recently been hospitalised because of alcohol-related damage. Has been in Harvey House and is trying to contact Inward House. David is dyslexic and needs help to fill forms. He is on DLA. I suggested AA and J2R. Suggested filling in housing association application for Wesley House, Sulyard St. (supported housing for over 50s); asked him to let us know his progress and to keep checking on progress with application.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE');
