('167', '19/11/2015 00:00', 'Graham', '', 'O', '', '', '', '1', '', 'C', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '20/10/2010 00:00', 'Kath', 'Recommendation from LDHAS. Called in for a 2 man tent, was in a rush, his friend calledJonathan relies on him.', 'T', 'Asked him to call back when he had more time. Won''t go to Edward Sreet', '', 'E', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '17/02/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'John is homeless as result of relationship break-up.  Returned to family in Bolton but had to leave due to a broken laptop.  His mother gave him some money for food and his benefit will be paid tomorrow - will transfer them to Lanc.  He has no alcohol/drug issues and only debt is a court fine.  Moved to Lancaster aged 13 and has friends here - can go to their''s for food, shower etc.  Knows a local farmer and will pitch his tent there.  C of E but has been to Father''s House - knows Dan from Soup Run.', 'H', 'Gave him advice - YMCA rent deposit scheme, registering as homeless at Strategic Housing, Morecambe, LDHAS - knows about.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '21/02/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'John called in for food - he has tried hunting and fishing with no success.  Talked about his family.  His sister takes drugs - "Bubble" (legal high).  When he was with his partner and children she broke in and robbed & set fire to his house.  His partner became depressed and he started drinking.  Does not know his real father and step-father ran away with a young Polish woman after 16 years.  Has supportive friends in Lanc.  Has provisional license and wants to take a course Lanc & Morecambe Coll to for his CS card.  Sees his children Tues and Thurs.', 'F', 'Gave him food.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '04/03/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Asked for food. Said he did not go to LDHAS today as he had an appointment with his solicitor.', 'F', 'Benefits - he has filled in  a form which has been sent to Preston. He should receive payment next week. Hopes then to apply for his CS card. He has nothing to occuply his time and doesn''t want to lose hope. Suggest courses and volunteering. He recognised they would look good on his CV. Solicitor will present his case to have his children returned - they were removed because his sister set fire to their home.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '24/03/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Asked if we could help with food - to make sandwiches. His circumstances are unchanged. He is depressed because he feels his children willbe put up for adoption (June hearing). He feels that he is being made to ''jump through hoops'' and that is he loses his children the past eight years will be pointless.', 'F', 'Suggested he registers with local doctor. LDHAS would provide a local list. Asks LDHAS to help with accommodation. He said he would go tomorrow. His former friends have seen him outside LDHAS and have spread rumours that he takes drugs. However, his drug tests have been clear. Blood tests for alcohol have not althouhg he says he is no longer drinking- has not done so since October. He goes for his third test on Monday.He is attended anger management course. He is thinking of doing the lime plastering and stonemasons course which are free. John said he had not achieved anything previously. Courses would give him a certificate. Asked if we could pray, he accepted.', 'E', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '05/04/2011 00:00', 'Jenny', 'John asked for help with a character reference form.', 'F', 'Gave him small food pack and he is returning on Wednesday weith character reference form from YMCA re: bond.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '11/04/2011 00:00', 'Jenny', 'John came in to see about funding for anger management. Had a chat. He has booked for two preventing classes and is going to the training tomorrow.', 'O', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '13/04/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'John came in with Sam Lang to collect his fishing tackle.  Spoke with Kath and Sylvia about finding a free anger management course.  Looking forward to seeing his girls soon.  Seems in much better spirits and is currently staying with Paul Tomlinson.', 'O', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '14/04/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'John came in as he has a contact number for open doors. Contacted them but can only help with bond if on probation. Kath gave him information for peer support (help people suffering with depression) He will look up website in Library. He began talking about religion. His mother suggested he join the Quakers. Talked about faith matters. Invited into the inner room for hospitality and longer conversation with Sylvia.', 'E', 'John was given a cup of coffee and biscuits while we talked about what helped him to feel closer to God (in relation to different types of churches). We also talked about other faiths, and science, and John seemed to enjoy the conversation, though he had to leave as he had an appointment with his solicitor.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '15/04/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'John came in today, after being paid he had gone to the pub. He spoke to Kath, Barbara, and Sylvia about his anger towards his ex in relation to his children. He said that he had come here as he needed to tell someone how he was feeling so he would not do anything. He tried to call his mum and Grandfather, but both numbers were unavailable/engaged.', 'E', 'He talked about his faith and prayed with him and talkedto him about his faith and why bad thimgs happen. He had an appointment to pick up a letter from the solicitors accross the road, Barbara went over but was not allowed to pick it up. We gave John three glasses of water and spoke with him for a long time before he left to get the letter himself. We also gave John a prayer card: ''God give me the serenity...etc'' and prayed for him after he left. Spoke to Lynette about John''s anger, he was particularly violent in his speech about what he would do to his ex-partner if his children were take into care. Lynette recommended that we explain to him out responsibilities if he should come in like that again and there be a resulting or inflammatory incident etc.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '21/04/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'John asked for bread etc to make sandwiches. He has been fishing in the canal.', 'F', 'John mentioned he would come to the Maundy Thursday evening service that night at St. Thomas'' where he took communion and had time to talk to the vicar. He also cam to the Ark on Friday and spoke with other guests and some of the volunteers about faith and where he sometimes struggles to believe.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '17/05/2011 00:00', 'Sylvia', 'John came in as he had been evicted along with Paul from the house he was staying in.He asked for a sleeping bag which we couldn''t provide.', 'S', 'Said we would pray for him and suggested he try Edward Street tomorrow.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '20/05/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'John asked for emergency food.', 'F', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '18/04/2012 00:00', 'Tina', 'John called in for bread.  Had received food from homeless action.  Stayed for brew and chat.', 'F', 'Gave bread.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '26/09/2012 00:00', 'Pam', '', 'F', 'Has not gone to Bolton yet, says he''s going tomorrow. Benefits stopped as he has put in a joint claim. Asked for food. Given for today and tomorrow up to lunch as he is going to Bolton!', '', '', '2', '', 'A', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '15/09/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'Barbara saw John at Edward Street yesterday and he called in to TOB today for a sleeping bag which we were unable to give him.  His children are waiting to be adopted - he is hoping they will stay together.  He talked about self-harm and solvent abuse.', 'S', 'Said we would pray for children.  We talked about putting the past behind him and prayed for him and his children.  He seemed calmer than when we''d seen him before.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '16/09/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Came in with Phil Barraclough.  He asked for help with bus fare to Bolton to collect clothes.  He talked about his relationship with his mother and how it had changed for the worse.  He hoped he would be able to go to Bolton tomorrow - already had a return rail ticket.', 'E', 'Told him that we''d prayed for his 3 children.  Gave him a jacket.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '04/10/2011 00:00', 'Gill', 'John called in initially for a deerstalker hat of which we had one! Plus  a scarf( unfortunately we didn''t have a neck warmer) he took an ordinary scarf. Had a cuppa, chatted relaxedly about his situation. Left to catch lunch at Edward St with a quickened resolve to talk to Christin? There in the hope of getting accomodation. He expressed determination nto to go down the excess drugs and drink route. He is plannin got do a "Lettering in stone" course. Would like to eventually make a career of this.', 'O', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '05/10/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'John called in with his younger sister Rhiannon. He will be staying with his sister. He asked for help with food. He spoke about his concerns re his last meeting with his 3 children - Lucia, Summer and Dylan before adoption. Suggested he register with a local doctor to help with depression. He would lika a proper diagnosis of his mental health issues. He stated that he used substances to block out what is happening in his life, his anger, etc.', 'F', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('168', '21/10/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'John asked for help with food. He is not staying with his sister but can go there to cook. He spoke about the anger he felt when he saw his 3 children for the last time. After Adoption Care have offered counselling but he no longer trusts them. Probation are also willing to find a counsellor. He is prepared to accept this.  He is paying back a compensation payment to an injured policeman. The incident happened 4 years ago and was assigned by the court.His own hand was cut during the incident requiring re-constructive surgery. He is still on the short list for his college course. Prayed for him before he left.', 'F', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
