('190', '01/04/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Jamie came in to give us news of Rose. He had been arrested in the London protest march and was wearing borrowed clothes. He was staying with a cousin in Lancaster and still undecided whether or not to return to London or Liverpool. He lived there previously (Liverpool) for 3-4years and was sober during that time. He spoke about his family. He was in care at 2 years. His mother and father were alcoholics. His father remained and his stepmother treated him in a way which made him feel iunwanted and rejected.', 'O', 'Gave him a Mark Gospel and journey into life, with contact details.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
