('192', '27/01/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Referred by LDHAS who have made a referral to RBL on his behalf.\nBenefit: ESA (lower rate), CAB appeal re higher rate. Serious work \nrelated accident summer 2010. Head injury affecting hearing - tinnitus and balance. Pre-dating depression following divorce. Left rented  accommodation with some arrears. Uses alcohol to self- medicate but has not since. He is qualified joiner and wants work. GP does not think he is fit for work.', 'U', 'Provided tent/sleeping bag, initial enqirer''s pack.', '', 'E', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('192', '25/02/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Called in with Phil.  John has viewed a flat in Morecambe.  LDHAS have contacted RBL on his behalf and the paper work is being \ncompleted.  He will start a 4 week pre-detox course at J2R soon.  His\n benefit appeal is in process - doctor says he is unfit but the Benefit \nagency say he is fit to to work.  Back trouble, head injury causing blackouts, depression and asthma.  If he does not return to work he will retrain as a plumber.  Feeling better about divorce.', 'H', 'Prayed for healing from depression.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
