('210', '14/08/2013 00:00', 'Pam', '', 'F', 'Lost his phone so phined it to leave a message. Is having marital problems so is sleeping in his friend''s shed for last 415 days. Left message with his mum. Smelt strongly of drink. Admotted to heavy drinking , numerous detoxes, prison sentences. Asked for food - gave sandwich making items - told him we couldn''t keep supporting him when he was in receipt of benefits & chos not to go back home.', '', '', '1', '', 'O', '', 'FALSE'),
('210', '17/03/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Will used to attend TOB meals.  Has drug/alcohol issues.  Homeless as a result of relationship breakdown - happened several times before.  Was with Addaction (court order).  Was in care for 3 months with his brother Mick.  His friend has allowed him to stay in his shed on an allotment - has been there a week.  Has an abscess but cannot go to dentist - wondered if doctor would give him antibiotics.', 'S', 'Gave food to make sandwiches.  Sleeping bag.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('210', '23/03/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'Will came for food.', 'F', 'Given food to make sandwiches c/beef, tin of ham, bread, milk.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('210', '01/04/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'Will says he is getting his money tomorrow and he has not had anything to eat since yesterday.', 'F', 'We got him some sandwiches and had a good chat about his alcohol addictionand psycotic episodes, he is not comfortable to be around people.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('210', '07/04/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Will''s benefits come in tomorrow. He asked if we could help out with breat etc. He has butter. Chatted about God, his daughter. He alwys checks to see if anyone is in. He likes cvoming in to TOB to chat with us. He is still in his shed but goes to his friend at night to watch TV. Helps him to relax. He tries to cut down his drinking when he goes to see his daughter. He recognises the moral code in the Bible. His brother and daughter keep him holding on.', 'F', 'Gave him milk, tuna, a pot of fruit salad, and bread .', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('210', '15/04/2011 00:00', 'Gill', 'Will called in today for more food for sandwiches. Talked a little bit (as a result of gentle questions from me) about his brother in the army and that they were both in a care home until they were 13, at which age he started drinking. Talked a little bit about detox but he says that it would be wasted on him as he doesn''t really want to give up. Has spent time in Harvey House twice before first time started taking heroine whilst in there (gave up soon after coming out and went back to alcohol abuse) Also shared about paranoia and need in the past to have people stay in the house with him at night, now he plays music to cut out anxious thoughts at night.', 'F', 'Gave him milk, bread, and some sandwich stuff.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('210', '20/04/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'Will came in today and was given a food parcel. He spoke of being frightened as going to use the service at Edward Street because of some of the people who go there. Will saw that some homeless people who he knows including himself are put off by some others who are not homeless.', 'F', 'Will came again for some bread and sandwich stuff etc. We were also able to give him some batteries for his MP3. His music calms him down, he is still very frightened around people and left when a few people came in but came back later.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('210', '04/05/2011 00:00', 'Sylvia', 'Will came in today and asked for food. We talked with him briefly and he said he would come back on Friday to talk more.', 'F', 'He had food and a loaf of bread.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('210', '06/05/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'Will came in for a chat, he has lost hope that he will ever be able to come of alcohol. I told him that we would be praying for him, but he doesn''t believe God will change his addictions.', 'F', 'We gave him a pie and some bread and meat for sandwiches and I gave him a ''Marks Gospel'' and ''Jorney into life''. He said he would read it.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('210', '13/05/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Will called in today asking for help -  to use TOB as postal address for his Giro and to use phone to contact benefit agency, food. He recieves his giro next Friday. Given two encouraging scriptures.', 'F', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
