('214', '31/03/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Tom came in just before we closed asking if we could help him to write a letter to Josie as they had had a falling out and it was a broken relationship. He expained what had been happening with Josie and that it was not sexual but for companionship and he wants to write a letter to Josie to encourage her to understand it all from his point of view and stop confusion about the situation. He wants to be friends again. Been to Relate and paid ', 'O', 'As Tom is new we took his details and arranged an appointment with him for 3pm Friday to come back and have an attempt to write the letter. We also want to talk with Tom if he wants to about how he is feeling and his lonliness and support for that.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('214', '01/04/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Tom came in today for his appointment, he sat with Sylvia and Barbara and Sylvia transcribed the letter for him. He is to come in on Monday to collect the three copies.', 'O', 'Tom was given a cup of coffee in the back room whilst we were writing, he also phoned in the late afternoon to ask if we could handwrite the letters.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('214', '03/04/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Tome came and collected letters from Sylvia- copies to go to seperate addresses and a copy for himself. Explained that we would not be able to write further letters on his behalf, he said he would like to come back in at a further point and talk to us about his own situation. He thanked us for helping him, and said he would photocopy the copy of the letter he had and send it again if he needed to.', 'O', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('214', '26/07/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'Tom Came again with the same request', 'O', 'Tom relationship with his woman friend has again deteriorated and he has asked that we write a letter for him so that she will again speak to him. We have had to refuse him and said that we could not get so involved in personal issues.  We recommended him to try YMCA and gave him a leaflet.', 'Y', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
