('220', '25/05/2012 00:00', 'Barbara', 'C.A.P.S.S referral. Benefits have been capped and bank charges have depleted family income.', 'F', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('221', '20/04/2011 00:00', 'Sylvia', 'Paul came for some food, he is living in someones drive. Barbara and I had a good spiritual chat. He was definately seeking. He is quite sporty and enjoying the weather but he does want to know more about God. He spoke about his past and his friend who had died two years ago and he was still quite emotional about it and it has impacted a lot on his life. He feelslost without his friend as they did so much together. He is active and likes canoing but doesn''t want to go alone. Broke his leg twice when he was playing football as a child and died three times during a car accident when he was two. Aslo advised him to go to the CAB to find out about financial support available.', 'F', 'We gave him a little food but he is a coleac so we didn''t have much to give him. We prayed for him and for healing for his coleacs disease. We gave him a welcome pack and two church easter leaflets, one for St. Tees and one for Christians Alive. Got coleacs disease - can''t eat wheat or gluten.', 'B', 'O', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('222', '21/04/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Jimmy is in a rented property with 3 others with no cooking facilities. He feels he needs to start taking medication again for his bi-polar. While in Manchester he was able to gradually withdraw all medication and felt well. He was with his brother. He returned to Lancaster for family reasons - his children. His brother has cancer of the bladder and his mother is not well. He is one of six brothers. One brother commited suicide. Jimmy is struggling at the moment and feels he is not getting the help he needs from his GP. His partner is in hospital (mental health). He has tried to support her emotionally and financially - she has not recieved her benefits yet. Suggested CAB.', 'F', 'Asked for help with food. We gave him bread, milk and a tin of tuna. Offered and recieved prayer. He repeated that he felt better.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('222', '13/06/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Jimmy came in for a chat. His neighbour Tony has mental issues and seems isolated. He has been in the commandos. We gave him part pack and introductary pack with ''journey into life'' for his neighbour.', 'F', '', '', '', '1', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
