('223', '27/04/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'Gordon has got into difficulty after a lady living with him has brought him into financial difficulties.  He has given CAP a ring but has not followed it through yet.', 'D', 'Gave him another leaflet and explained how CAP works.  Gave him a food parcel.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('224', '28/04/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Tyla came in with Joanne Finch, her Disc floating support worker.  Tyla is 18 and looking after her 14 year old brother Michael after the death of their mother.  They do not know their fathers. They lost some money and a phone on a trip to Blackpool.', 'F', 'Emergency food for Tyla and her brother.  We are here if she needs some to talk to.  We will pray.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('225', '27/04/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'John was passing and saw our notice about addictions.  Struggling with long-term gambling addiction - 15 years old used a slot machine then got a well paid job and started casino gambling.  He always tried to cover his outgoings and set limits which he always broke.  Enjoys the excitement of risk even when he loses.', 'A', 'Gave number for university counselling service.  Info re Celebrate Recovery - brought up Catholic.  We said we''d pray.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('226', '28/04/2011 00:00', 'Sylvia', 'Came in looking for someone to assist him in a meeting with work - legal side.  Alan is an alcoholic who needs support in relation to his job.  Has a meeting next Wed 10am.  Done it own accord to try and sort alcoholism.  Been in UK 15 years.  Alan goes to J2R and is looking at detox and rehab.  Not sure how this will affect his but hopefully the meeting on Wed will sort out these issues.  Said he would come back to update us.', 'D', 'Gave CAP leaflet and welcome pack.  Advised him to take a friend to the meeting as we cannot.  Prayed with him for future, addiction, peace and hope. Texted info about TLC Resettlement project at LDHAS.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('227', '05/05/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Phone Referral from Alice: Child Protection Socail Services, White Cross.', 'D', 'Gave social worker CAP leaflet and said would email information on new Money Management (CAP). Given 1 Standard pack and 2 half packs of food plus bread and milk.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
