('263', '30/09/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Paul came in for food chat and hospitality. He spoke about the death of his mother from a heart attack during a burglary. How he felt about it how he was in prison at the time- how he took things to block his memories and feelings - how the burglar had not regard his mother lying while he was in her home.', 'F', 'Prayed for him before he left for strength and made up a part bag of food.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('263', '06/10/2011 00:00', 'Emma', 'Paul came in for a chat/coffee. He spoke about his depression/anxiety. He said his anxiety started when he was about 17 - he was walking along the street in Lancaster and was bundled into a van. His arms and legs were tied together and he was robbed of everything but his underwear and trainers. Walked to the neares farm where he was dropped and got a lift back into Lancaster. This was obviously traumatic and has left him fearful - we prayed for healing from the memories/peace.', 'E', 'Gave him a few tins and a large print Gideon''s Bible and some little prayer cards. We encouraged him to pray out loud in his room.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('263', '20/10/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Paul came for chat and hosptality. Stayed fro prayer. Spoke again about feeling intimidated, bullied and being afraid of going home. Spoke about his suicidal thoughts and fear of self-harming. He has completed the application for Stonham, Kendal. His support worker at Stonham knows he is being bullied. He mentioned throwing things in his room against the wall, knives etc or thinking about it.', 'P', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('263', '31/10/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Paul came for a chat. Asked for and given a few tins. His interview for Stonham, Kendal is tomorrow. Grace-Leanne, his support worker will be going with him.', 'F', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('263', '02/11/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'Asked for food. Food taken by other residents. He wants to cook for his friend.', 'F', 'Given some food.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('263', '14/11/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'Paul requested some food.  He is moving to Kendal on Wednesday because of the bullying.  He is worried about his benefit arriving on Friday after he has gone.', 'F', 'Gave him a couple of days food to tide him over.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('263', '15/11/2011 00:00', 'Jenny', 'Paul called in with friend Barry Pearson.', 'F', 'Gave him food to take with him to Stonham housing Kendal (Riverview).  Prayed for him and told Barry to keep us informed of Paul''s progress in Kendal.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
