('267', '10/08/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Mark has had his wallet stolen with all his money in and needed some emergency food.  He talked about his past life and he has had alcohol problems but turned his life around in prison.  His father was involved in the Miner''s Srike and he has memories of being impoverished.  He is meeting up with his brother who he hasn''t seen since he was 8.  Also made contact with ex and 12 year old son.  Has been drinking for 15 years but has been clear for a year.  Attending SMART at EDHAS.  Is at Langley Trust accommodation but will be moving shortly.', 'F', 'Gave emergency food and listened.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('267', '15/08/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Mark came in today for some more food. His benifits came thru on 17/8/11 Wed. He brought us a CD player for the shop. Gave him a book-"Nobody''s Child" a testimony. He said he would read it.', 'F', 'Gave him food and a book.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('267', '24/08/2011 00:00', 'Kath', 'Mark came in and brought us a desk fan.  He is struggling as they are taking too much out of his benifits to be able to cope.', 'D', 'We chatted about the Gospel and he asked for a Bible. We gave him a Bible.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('267', '25/08/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Mark asked for emergancy food.  He had brought down his paperwork as proof, he has a form to complete to reduce the payments out of his benifits from 40.00 to 10 pounds per fortnight.  He needs help till next Wednesday', 'F', 'Gave Mark emergancy food.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('267', '26/08/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Mark agreed to be videod on our behalf for the Spirit of Lancashire Awards.  He was concerned that he did not have enough food to last over the weekend.', 'F', 'Gave extra food.  He has completed form to transfer from J S A to Sickness Benifit.', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('267', '03/10/2011 00:00', 'Debbie', 'Mark came in . He has got a job at the chicken factory. He goes an his bike. The job is full time but his benefits have stopped and he needed some food til he gets his first pay. He looks as though in the neat 2 months he will have a house/flat of his own. Mark ended up going into pubs in town and one night he did get drunk and was nearly put back in prison but he was given a second chance but will be put away if it happens again.', 'F', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('267', '07/10/2011 00:00', 'Pam', 'Needs some food to tide him over until he gets his first pay. Seemed well and [positive.', 'F', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
('267', '28/10/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Mark came in for coffee. Later asked for food. His agency work is not consistent. Long conversationnabout his life, past work as a salesman, work with probation. He asked if he could take a "Pathway to Peace" and "3 o''clock in the morning". The Mark Gospel lies unopened on his table', 'F', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
