('277', '01/09/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Referred by Probation Service.  Linda''s son brought her.  Applied for a crisis loan but has applied 3 times before so likely to be refused.  Has been on DLA for 5 years but was stopped in 2010.  She appealed but was refused after 16 weeks.  Appealing again with help of Probation Service and medical evidence.  Has osteo-arthritis and is being tested for cancer because of bleeding after the menopause.  Several members of family have cancer including father who died from it.  Linda felt she had noone to turn to because she doesn''t want to be a burden.  She has recently been through a court case which was publicised and some members of her family no longer talk to her.  She borrowed from a friend who turned out to be an "enemy" - has paid debt now.  Ex-husband living with her or he would be homeless.  She reported feeling "peace" in TOB and that it was "awesome" and that she felt better than when she came in.', 'F', 'Gave emergency food.  Prayed.  Said she could return again for chat or if she needed help.', '', 'O', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
