('297', '07/10/2011 00:00', 'Barbara', 'Tony came to ask for advice re relationship situaton at his home (Langley House Trust).\nHe had put in an official complaint on the advice of his key worker - re the inappropriate dress of a woman worker. Several similar complaints had been made. Management had taken his complaint seriously, spoken to the woman( who was now on annual leave) and issued a first warning.\nTony was concerned that the woman would know it was him and how she would react.\nHe spoke about the courses he was taking to build up his CV. He has finished a City and Guilds painting and decorating course, about to start a cookery course and taking horse riding lessons.\nHe has ben at Langley house 5 years and is thinking about living independently.\nWe said we would pray about the situation - his peace of mind and a roght solutiion', 'E', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FALSE'),
